BRIEFLY 
Ex-Merrill Lynch Official Admits Payoffs: Albert Young, 61, of New York and 
Hawley, Pa., a former Merrill vice president, pleaded guilty to mail fraud, 
bribery and tax evasion. Young said he received about $127,500 in payoffs from 
contractors who built the brokerage's headquarters in Manhattan's World 
Financial Center. He faces up to 18 years in prison and a fine of $1 million. 
